SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2354.2012.00722.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This article investigates the relationship between the Herfindahl?Hirschman Index (HHI) and welfare in multiple-leader Stackelberg models. We formulate two long-run models of free entry of followers; in the first (second) model, leaders select their output before (after) the entry of the followers. We find that in both models, in contrast to the short-run models, the Stackelberg model yields a larger welfare and HHI than the Cournot model does regardless of the number of leaders; that is, beneficial concentration always occurs.
ER  - 

